# API Architecture Rules

Apply these rules when editing backend API code.

## Layer Boundaries

- Keep request parsing and response shaping in routing/view modules.
- Keep business decisions in logic modules.
- Keep external integrations and subsystem orchestration in services.
- Keep complex query construction in data access modules.
- Keep schema and business validation in validators.
- Keep reusable utilities in shared tools modules.

## Query and Performance Discipline

- Minimize database round trips; prefer bulk loading and set-based operations.
- Avoid hidden N+1 access patterns; use explicit prefetch/select strategies.
- Keep transformations close to the most efficient layer (query or logic) to avoid redundant passes.

## Change Hygiene

- Preserve existing API contracts unless the change explicitly requires a contract update.
- When contracts change, update docs/tests/changelog entries in the same workstream.
